WEBVTT



00:00:09.952 --> 00:00:13.248
Welcome to the Canopy Roads Baptist Church podcast.

00:00:13.376 --> 00:00:17.472
Our mission is to develop fully devoted followers of Christ.

00:00:17.888 --> 00:00:26.176
Welcome back to the podcast. On today's episode, we are excited to have Jenny Pratz reading Psalm 141 as part of our Psalms Project journey.

00:00:30.080 --> 00:00:32.000
Psalm 141.

00:00:32.128 --> 00:00:34.880
Prayer for preservation from evil

00:00:34.848 --> 00:00:36.704
A psalm of David.

00:00:36.768 --> 00:00:40.384
I call upon you, O Lord, come quickly to me.

00:00:40.288 --> 00:00:43.264
Give ear to my voice when I call to you.

00:00:43.200 --> 00:00:51.168
Let my prayer be counted as incense before you, and the lifting up of my hands as an evening sacrifice.

00:00:51.136 --> 00:00:56.416
Let a guard over my mouth, O Lord, keep watch over the door of my lips.

00:00:56.224 --> 00:01:01.536
Do not turn my heart to any evil to busy myself with wicked deeds.

00:01:01.600 --> 00:01:04.640
In company with those who work iniquity.

00:01:04.512 --> 00:01:07.584
Do not let me eat of their delicacies.

00:01:07.456 --> 00:01:09.664
Let the righteous strike me

00:01:09.536 --> 00:01:11.936
Let the faithful correct me.

00:01:11.840 --> 00:01:15.456
Never let the oil of the wicked anoint my head.

00:01:15.264 --> 00:01:19.712
For my prayer is continually against their wicked deeds.

00:01:19.584 --> 00:01:23.104
When they are given over to those who shall condemn them

00:01:23.712 --> 00:01:26.464
Then they shall learn that my.

00:01:26.848 --> 00:01:28.736
Worth words

00:01:28.576 --> 00:01:29.920
Were pleasant.

00:01:29.824 --> 00:01:33.728
Like a rock that one breaks apart and shatters on the land,

00:01:33.504 --> 00:01:37.440
So shall their bones be strewn at the mouth of Sheol.

00:01:37.536 --> 00:01:41.024
"'But my eyes are turned toward you, O God, my Lord.'"

00:01:40.928 --> 00:01:42.976
In you i seek refuge.

00:01:42.816 --> 00:01:45.024
Do not leave me defenseless.

00:01:45.344 --> 00:01:48.896
Keep from me the trap that they have laid for me.

00:01:48.672 --> 00:01:51.296
And from the snares of evil-doers

00:01:51.104 --> 00:01:54.048
Let the wicked fall into their own nets

00:01:53.760 --> 00:01:56.064
while I alone escape.

00:01:57.408 --> 00:01:59.840
Questions to ponder after that.

00:02:00.032 --> 00:02:03.488
What temptations are hard for you to overcome?

00:02:03.744 --> 00:02:06.176
Can God actually guard you?

00:02:06.208 --> 00:02:08.352
And keep watch over you.

00:02:17.152 --> 00:02:25.280
We hope this message was encouraging to you. If you would like this kind of content delivered directly to you, consider subscribing to our channel.

00:02:25.376 --> 00:02:34.816
If you'd like more information about our church, please visit us on the web at canopyroads.org. And thanks for listening to the Canopy Roads Baptist Church podcast.
